content: My daughter absolutely loves this app! She can play it for hours. Only problem I have, (every single month) is when the automatic payment goes through, it doesn't reflect on the account for a day or 2, so all her mini games are locked and I sometimes have to uninstall and reinstall a couple of times. It really is annoying. If she didn't love it so much, I would have canceled a long time ago, with how much trouble it gives me once a month. Please fix that issue.

The app itself is great, lots of cause-and-effect play, and I love the freeform nature of everything. There's nothing to win or lose, just fun and interesting environments to explore. Customer service helped me resolve an issue really quickly as well, I'm happy to pay the subscription price for a nice app that doesn't make annoying sounds or have questionable content!
replyContent: Thank you so much for the kind words! :)

content: This app is perfect for young kids and kids with special needs. It has so many different interactive options and worlds to choose from. Also love that the content changes often. It does require a lot of space but you can pick what you want to add or remove. We also have Sago Mini School app and ‚ù§ it!

My ASD daughter absolutely loves this app! There is so much to explore and she absolutely loves the "open sandbox" platform and delights when she discovers something new within one of the worlds. There are a variety of different worlds and characters to choose from, so none of the content ever seems stale to her. I love it because it creates an opportunity for me to encourage spontaneous dialogue with her and engaging her to interact and speak with me and let me into her world. I had an issue accessing some of the games after a few days - my free trial had expired and there was some delay in my subscription updating. I contacted the support personnel and received a response same day with an apology and resolution to my issue! While the cost of the app is higher than any I have paid for before, the option I chose was annual and TOTALLY worth it for the amount of content you are getting and the interaction opportunities it is creating for me with my daughter. World class product and service, I would more stars if I could!

content: A great idea with one major flaw. There is no incentive for Sago Mini lovers who already have most of the apps to subscribe. Feel a little let down as a long time loyal fan.

Edit: After emailing sago mini, they were able to fix the problem. This app makes my lo happy, so I don't mind paying for subscription. Added bonus is you get ALL games into 1 app. I used to love this app, but now my son can't download any games. Keeps saying no space, delete unused apps. I have over 50 GB of space, not sure why I can't download all apps, especially when I paid for a years subscription.
replyContent: Hi Pricilla, just wanted to follow-up and let you know that we've shrunk the size of our Android app considerably. After the initial download, you‚Äôll be able to download games individually that you‚Äôd like to be able to play offline! content: Dream app for pre-schoolers ages 2-4. I have a 3 year old who is in love with this app (as well as School). Mom is too. The device + preschooler combo is filled with guilt over the social pressure, so when we found these I could have cried for joy. They are amazing quality, no ads, lots of variety and open ended play, interactive, teach various subjects and environments where they can manipulate the surroundings or build and interact with the characters. It is WELL worth the subscription.

The games are really good and they add more quite often. My son who just turned 4 loves it and often asks to play. He can do everything by himself which is a big plus. The only thing I dislike is that it's quite pricey. I think at half the price I would just keep it indefinitely but at this price I'm expecting to cancel as soon as my son loses interest.

I will never have a problem paying for this game bc it is so much fun for my toddler. Very educational but not in a way you would think. Keeps my 2 year old busy for long periods of time. content: It's a great idea to offer a subscription to all the excellent sago mini apps. It works out better than buying them all individually and it means I can lock the phone down to just one app when handing over my phone to me toddler. As always, the characters have such personality

This game is a collection of the smaller games offered by Sago. Each game is a sandbox world where players can interact with every item they see. there isn't always an objective to "win." Cons- the subscription is too expensive. My child gets frustrated at times because it can be hard to find her favorite places/games. I don't think they add content to old games. Pros - the content is updated regularly, adding the new games that Sago has released. You could buy each game separately.

The art style is clean and the colors are playful without being overbearing. The music is never obnoxious or loud. It's something I could enjoy listening to all day! The characters are fun and sweet and they have nice voices. The open ended play gives me glances into my child's surprising and delightful imagination.
